This fixture is a single-file Go module with an interface method implemented by
a concrete type. textDocument/implementation on the interface method must
resolve to the concrete method implementation, exercising gopls implementation
support rather than definition support.

Markers embedded in the source drive the test:

  query=Greet  marks the interface method occurrence to query.
  target=Greet marks the concrete method implementation the request must
               resolve to.

-- go.mod --
module implementationinterface

go 1.27

-- main.go --
package main

type Greeter interface {
	Greet() string // query=Greet
}

type english struct{}

func (english) Greet() string { // target=Greet
	return "hello"
}

func main() {
	var greeter Greeter = english{}
	println(greeter.Greet())
}
